.TH VALKEY-CLI 1 "2024"
.SH NAME
valkey-cli \- Command-line client for Valkey
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B valkey-cli
.RI [options] [cmd [arg [arg ...]]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Valkey is a high-performance, open-source key-value data store.
It supports strings, hashes, lists, sets, sorted sets, streams,
and other data structures.
.PP
\fBvalkey-cli\fP is the Valkey command-line client.
It can be used interactively or non-interactively to send commands
to a Valkey server and display the replies.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-h hostname
Server hostname (default 127.0.0.1).
.TP
\-p port
Server port (default 6379).
.TP
\-s socket
Server socket (overrides host and port).
.TP
\-a password
Password to use when connecting to the server (see SECURITY WARNING below).
.TP
\-\-pass password
Same as \-a.
.TP
\-u uri
Server URI (valkey://user:secret@localhost:6379/0).
.TP
\-n db
Database number (default 0).
.TP
\-3
Start session in RESP3 protocol mode.
.TP
\-\-tls
Enable TLS (requires TLS support compiled in).
.TP
\-\-cacert file
CA certificate file for TLS verification.
.TP
\-\-cert file
Client certificate file for TLS.
.TP
\-\-key file
Client private key file for TLS.
.TP
\-r repeat
Execute specified command \fIrepeat\fP times.
.TP
\-i interval
When \-r is used, sleep \fIinterval\fP seconds between commands.
.TP
\-\-no\-auth\-warning
Do not show the security warning when using \-a.
.TP
\-\-stat
Print rolling stats about server: memory, clients, requests per second.
.TP
\-\-latency
Enter a mode that continuously samples latency.
.TP
\-\-latency\-history
Like \-\-latency but tracks latency over time and resets every 15 seconds.
.TP
\-\-latency\-dist
Shows latency as a spectrum; requires 256-color terminal.
.TP
\-\-lru\-test count
Simulate a cache workload with the specified number of keys.
.TP
\-\-replica
Simulate a replica showing commands received from the master.
.TP
\-\-rdb filename
Transfer an RDB dump from remote server to local file.
.TP
\-\-hotkeys
Fetch hot keys (requires \fBmaxmemory\-policy\fP to use LFU).
.TP
\-\-bigkeys
Sample keys looking for keys with many elements (big keys).
.TP
\-\-memkeys
Sample keys looking for keys consuming a lot of memory.
.TP
\-\-scan
List all keys using the SCAN command.
.TP
\-\-pattern pat
Useful with \-\-scan, \-\-bigkeys or \-\-hotkeys (default *).
.TP
\-\-intrinsic\-latency sec
Run a test to measure intrinsic system latency for \fIsec\fP seconds.
.TP
\-\-eval file
Send an Eval command using the Lua script stored in \fIfile\fP.
.TP
\-\-pipe
Transfer raw Redis/RESP protocol from stdin to server.
.TP
\-\-pipe\-timeout n
Abort with error if after sending all data to the server no reply is
received within \fIn\fP seconds (default 30; use 0 to wait forever).
.TP
\-\-cluster
Cluster manager commands and options.
.TP
\-\-verbose
Verbose mode.
.TP
\-\-no\-cluster\-move
Disable the implicit move of hash-slot to a different node when a
MOVED error is received.
.TP
\-\-resp2
Use RESP2 protocol.
.TP
\-\-resp3
Use RESP3 protocol (same as \-3).
.SH SECURITY WARNING
Using \-a or \-\-pass to supply a password on the command line is insecure
and will generate a warning. The password may be visible to other users
via \fBps\fP(1) or similar tools. Prefer using the \fBVALKEY_URL\fP
environment variable or the \fIauthenticate\fP command after connecting.
